@startuml
title UC2 - View Review Comments

start

:1. Developer opens Pull Request page;
:2. System fetches review comments;
:3. System loads all feedback from analyzers;

if (4. Comments exist?) then (Yes)
  :5. Organize comments by severity;
else (No)
  :6. Display "No issues found";
  stop
endif

:7. Display all comments with details;
:8. Show code context and suggestions;

if (9. Developer wants to filter?) then (Yes)
  :10. Apply selected filter criteria;
  :11. Re-display filtered comments;
else (No)
endif

:12. Developer reviews the feedback;
:13. Mark comments as viewed;

stop

note right
Activity Description:

1. Developer opens the Pull Request page.
2. System fetches all review comments from database.
3. System loads feedback from all analyzers.
4. System checks if any comments exist.
5. If no comments - displays success message and stops.
6. System organizes comments by severity level.
7. System displays all comments with details.
8. System shows code context and improvement suggestions.
9. System checks if developer wants to filter comments.
10. If yes - applies selected filter criteria.
11. If yes - re-displays filtered comments.
12. Developer reviews the feedback.
13. System marks comments as viewed.
end note

@enduml
